INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4362','2235','Issue','421','The access works fine. \r\nI\'m using it for this application: http://code.google.com/p/redmine-connect\r\n(Redmine -> Microsoft Project converter). This is a desktop app, which creates a \"demo\" config on install. This demo-config has hostedredmine.com credentials so users can try simple queries to grab issues from \"taskconnector-test\" project and save in a MS Project file.\r\nI can also add a link to hostedredmine.com webpage to the Help pages of that app.\r\nI\'m not sure if I would use hostedredmine.com for \"TaskConnector\" development itself. Redmine system would be convenient for me than googlecode, but I\'m not sure how stable this site is and how long it will last.','2010-07-29 11:51:25');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4364','2235','Issue','3','Alexey Java wrote:\r\n> I\'m using it for this application: http://code.google.com/p/redmine-connect\r\n> (Redmine -> Microsoft Project converter). This is a desktop app, which creates a \"demo\" config on install. This demo-config has hostedredmine.com credentials so users can try simple queries to grab issues from \"taskconnector-test\" project and save in a MS Project file.\r\n\r\nSounds really interesting.\r\n\r\n> I can also add a link to hostedredmine.com webpage to the Help pages of that app.\r\n\r\nThat would be nice.\r\n\r\n> I\'m not sure if I would use hostedredmine.com for \"TaskConnector\" development itself. Redmine system would be convenient for me than googlecode, but I\'m not sure how stable this site is and how long it will last.\r\n\r\nThis site has been in existence for about 5 months. I\'ve been a user of Redmine for years. I don\'t plan to close down this website. The users are growing in numbers (about 400) and it is becoming more popular. A few other people are running open-source projects from here.','2010-07-29 17:58:00');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4918','2645','Issue','3','I can see in my web broswer: https://www.hostedredmine.com/issues.xml\r\n\r\nYou problem seems to be here:\r\nhttps://www.hostedredmine.com/attachments/651/RunMe.java#L148\r\n\r\nYou are trying to log into Redmine using:\r\nuserName = \"java\";\r\npassword = \"java\";\r\n\r\nYou don\'t need to authenticate to view issues.xml?\r\n\r\nI haven\'t done anything with the API on Redmine before, so I\'ll do some research if you need further help?','2010-08-13 08:27:45');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4919','2645','Issue','421','well, you don\'t have to send authentication info to see issues list. plus it\'s done via GET request, so you could pass \"key\" parameter in the GET request line. I verified it works fine.\r\nWhat I\'m trying to do is to perform a POST request to create an issue and I see that Basic Authentication is blocked by that website and at the same time I don\'t know how to provide \"key\" in the POST body. ','2010-08-13 08:30:54');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4920','2645','Issue','3','Well, \"Enable REST web service\" is enabled in Redmine settings.\r\n\r\nAhh... Go here:\r\nhttps://www.hostedredmine.com/my/account\r\n\r\nIn the right column, see \"RSS access key\" and \"API access key\". I\'m guessing \"API access key\" is what you need.','2010-08-13 08:35:07');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4921','2645','Issue','421','yep, I know. the problem is how to provide that info in HTTP POST request. in GET this is not a problem - adding \"key=.....\" to the URL solved the authentication issue.\r\nbut I need \"HTTP POST\" request because this is how Redmine REST API creates issues.\r\n\r\nI tried adding this parameter into the URL, and according to the Redmine source code this should be (!) used even when I perform a \"POST\", but in fact this does not work. that\'s why I\'m trying to use HTTP Basic Authentication, which is *supposedly* blocked by www.hostedredmine.org','2010-08-13 08:38:46');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4924','2645','Issue','421','Eric Davis just gave example how to provide API access key in POST requests: http://www.redmine.org/issues/5997#note-11\r\nI will try it.','2010-08-13 09:50:26');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4928','2645','Issue','421','no luck.\n\n<pre>\nPOST https://293a64eef15b452047a0315ecc6eff2a9bbd4a9c:X@www.hostedredmine.com/issues.xml HTTP/1.1  -> <issue><project_id>taskconnector-test</project_id><subject>test zzx</subject><assigned_to name=\"Alexey Java\" id=\"421\"/></issue>\njavax.net.ssl.SSLPeerUnverifiedException: peer not authenticated\n</pre>','2010-08-13 14:45:53');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('4933','2645','Issue','3','Sorry I haven\'t been available much today.\r\n\r\nI take it you\'ve read: http://www.redmine.org/wiki/redmine/Rest_Issues\r\n\r\nAs per the document, in GET you do:\r\n<pre>\r\nGET /issues.xml?key=1a022b4661da64e5dca53ebab0c94ad7\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nIn post, you do something like:\r\n<pre>\r\n	POST /login.jsp HTTP/1.1\r\n	Host: www.mysite.com\r\n	User-Agent: Mozilla/4.0\r\n	Content-Length: 27\r\n	Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\r\n\r\n	key=1a022b4661da64e5dca53ebab0c94ad7\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nYou need to send it as a HTTP header. Thus it is encrypted.','2010-08-13 18:12:23');
INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('5105','2645','Issue','421','Have you tried your last variant to create issues via REST API? looks like it\'s something to be sent from browser, while REST API expects text/xml content-type, plus not clear where to provide the issue body.\n\nI\'m trying to send request basing on Eric\'s (Redmine developer) code:\n\n>curl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: text/xml\" -d \"<issue><subject>api</subject><project_id>taskconnector-test</project_id></issue>\" https://fc20e8f5f1885fc194b7b7865e6d6ce9a44a4b88:X@www.hostedredmine.com/issues.xml\n\n\nthis works with HTTP protocol on my local server, but fails with HTTPS on www.hostedredmine.com. \nI don\'t know if it\'s a server configuration issue or Redmine bug.','2010-08-17 10:37:07');
