INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES ('18043','8533','Issue','3','Alexey,\r\n\r\nI\'ve added a new role called \"Guest\" which is the same as \"Reporter\" but without the repository permissions. This role will never have repository permissions.\r\n\r\nThis option is only sensible for _private_ projects, because public ones allow non-members and anonymous access to the Repository in the current configuration. This suites open-source projects and alike.\r\n\r\nLet me know if this satisfies your request.\r\n\r\nI\'ll upload a screenshot of the HostedRedmine.com permissions here: [[Permissions]]\r\n\r\n\r\nTyler,\r\n\r\nWe allow \"non members\" to add and comment on issues. That means, for public projects, anyone with a HostedRedmine.com account can add issues. I don\'t however like allowing anonymous users to have write access to anything, but if you disagree, be sure to give me your reasoning and I\'ll reconsider.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nBrad','2011-01-13 18:55:56');
