INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('105','1',NULL,'Mark unread topics/messages in the forum','Is there an way to mark unread topics/messages in the Forum?\r\n\r\nBecause it would be nice to just login and see which topic/messages are new. I know there is a watch feature, which i found very nice for contributing to a project or watch a specific item.\r\n\r\nBut seeing unread topic/messages are much more practical for a forum, specially for a closed one ;)','350','5','111','2010-07-16 02:02:16','2010-07-19 08:05:10','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('107','1','105','RE: Mark unread topics/messages in the forum','No, most forums don\'t offer that feature. There are two reasons:\r\n\r\n1) You would have to be always logged in for the system to know who you are, thus to determine what you\'ve looked at.\r\n\r\n2) The database would have to record every message you have ever looked at permanently. If you had 10,000 users, with 15,000 messages (say 5,000 posts), then you are storing 150,000,000 rows in your database for that info. Given the hassle of backups and extra memory etc... its not a feature that passes cost/benefit usually.\r\n\r\nAnything I missed?','3','0',NULL,'2010-07-16 18:50:16','2010-07-16 18:50:16','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('108','1','105','RE: Mark unread topics/messages in the forum','I have however got \"Message added\" email notifications enabled. So try going to \"My account\" and select \"For any event on all my projects\". This will let you receive an email whenever anyone posts a new topic.','3','0',NULL,'2010-07-16 18:53:44','2010-07-16 18:53:44','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('109','1','105','RE: Mark unread topics/messages in the forum','Ah, thanks. Good to know.\r\n\r\nOn point 2 you missed that there must only be one row for each post saved (which point to the last message you seen). So it\'s \"only\" 50,000,000 rows in this case and should even a faster solution. But you are right that\'s some kind of overhead.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think about a light weight version which only shows new post/messages since last visit? This only require to check each post/messages against the timestamp of the last visit (the timestamp is already there?).\r\nFor a forum where you don\'t read each message it\'s even better, because you don\'t must visit (or unmark) all the post that don\'t interrest you. But overall it would only a small benefit i think.\r\n\r\nWhatever, thanks for the great service you offer :)','350','0',NULL,'2010-07-16 19:48:31','2010-07-16 19:48:31','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('110','1','105','RE: Mark unread topics/messages in the forum','Sven Gleitsmann wrote:\r\n> On point 2 you missed that there must only be one row for each post saved (which point to the last message you seen). So it\'s \"only\" 50,000,000 rows in this case and should even a faster solution. But you are right that\'s some kind of overhead.\r\n\r\nYou are right.\r\n\r\n> What do you think about a light weight version which only shows new post/messages since last visit? This only require to check each post/messages against the timestamp of the last visit (the timestamp is already there?).\r\n> For a forum where you don\'t read each message it\'s even better, because you don\'t must visit (or unmark) all the post that don\'t interrest you. But overall it would only a small benefit i think.\r\n\r\nInteresting idea.\r\n\r\nI suggest you head over to Redmine and suggest it as a new \"Feature\":\r\nhttp://www.redmine.org/projects/redmine/issues/new','3','0',NULL,'2010-07-16 19:54:32','2010-07-16 19:54:32','0','0');
