INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('1177','1',NULL,'How to add a tracker?','Can someone please tell me how to add a new tracker in my project?\r\n\r\nI guess it must be quite simple as everywhere I read a similar topic, it starts with \"I created a tracker, but....\"\r\nBut somehow I can\'t seem to figure it out. \r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nMukesh','3500','2','1192','2011-06-29 18:31:57','2011-06-30 13:54:50','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('1190','1','1177','RE: How to add a tracker?','Mukesh,\r\n\r\nOnly a HostedRedmine.com administrator can add new tracker types.\r\n\r\nYou can turn different trackers on and off from your project\'s Settings tab, under Trackers.\r\n\r\nIs there another tracker type you would like to see?\r\n\r\nBrad','3','0',NULL,'2011-06-30 07:35:42','2011-06-30 07:35:42','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('1192','1','1177','RE: How to add a tracker?','Ya I was thinking I could use another tracker type.\r\nBasically I am making different processes in my company for making changes to the production code on the basis of whether it is \"feature\", \"bug\" etc.\r\nSo in that I wanted to add a category of \"config changes\". This way I can prioritize them like a bug, but not really calling them bug since they are not.\r\n\r\nMaybe a minor use case.','3500','0',NULL,'2011-06-30 13:54:50','2011-06-30 13:54:50','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('1197','1',NULL,'How to define the workflow?','I see some workflow settings on http://www.redmine.org/projects/redmine/wiki/RedmineIssueTrackingSetup\r\nThat looks nice, however I am unable to find that in HostedRedmine. Where should I go to locate that?\r\n','3500','2','1206','2011-06-30 16:46:03','2011-06-30 18:37:08','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('1199','1',NULL,'How does Support ticketing work?','Just curious to understand how is the tracker type \"support\" supposed to work.\r\n\r\nThere are two ways that come to my mind:\r\n1) Users can be given link to the project\'s \"issues-page\" where people can post their support queries\r\n\r\n2) Users can be asked to mail to support@example.com and some system should automatically create a support-ticket in the issue-page of example.com\r\n\r\nI think second one is neater, and also user won\'t need to go to a different url if the backend-support system changes. \r\n\r\nWhich of these two is possible to do with HostedRedmine?\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nMukesh','3500','2','1205','2011-06-30 16:50:51','2011-06-30 18:34:26','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('1200','1',NULL,'Repository feature (Git)','Hi everyone,\r\n\r\nI tried following the instructions given by Redmine when we try to activate the \"Repository\" feature.\r\n\r\nBut when I do the command : git push (with the git@rails.bitbot.net.au:identifierofmyproject.git as target) I am thrown away by the server :\r\n<pre>\r\nPermission denied (publickey).\r\nfatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nOf course, I\'ve already uploaded my SSH Public Keys. And I also added myself as a \"developper\" to the project ... \r\n\r\nMaybe the feature is just disabled at HostedRedmine.com ? (Free Account)\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks in advance for answers :) \r\n\r\nTD','3513','2','1204','2011-06-30 17:41:26','2011-06-30 18:25:04','0','0');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES ('1201','1','1199','RE: How does Support ticketing work?','Mukesh,\r\n\r\nRedmine can do both of those things, however, HostedRedmine.com can only support the first.\r\n\r\nWe are considering allowing issue updates by email, but haven\'t yet done this.\r\n\r\nBrad','3','0',NULL,'2011-06-30 18:03:13','2011-06-30 18:03:13','0','0');
